#How to create files in nodeJS

Documentation of NodeJs on File System
https://nodejs.org/api/fs.html#fs_file_system

Some Lecture
https://docs.nodejitsu.com/articles/file-system/how-to-write-files-in-nodejs

Video Instruction Sample
https://youtu.be/o7NIYGLC13o

require("fs");

to create a folder - fs.mkdir("folderName");
to delete a folder - fs.rmdir("folderName");

to create a file - fs.writeFileSync("fileName.extension");
to remove a file - fs.unlink("fileName.extension");

to read a file - fs.readFileSync("fileName.extension", "UTF-8") 
//Second parameter - "UTF-8" to read character set

To remove a directory (folder) that is not a character set:
http://www.geedew.com/remove-a-directory-that-is-not-empty-in-nodejs/
